    <h1>Nepal</h1>
    <p>Nepal is a beautiful landlocked country located in South Asia between India and China. It is known for its breathtaking
        <br>
    natural beauty, rich cultural heritage, and friendly people. Nepal is home to the world's highest mountain, Mount
    Everest, which attracts thousands of climbers and trekkers every year. The country has diverse landscapes, including the
    Himalayan mountains, green hills, fertile plains, rivers, and forests. Nepal is also famous for its many temples,
    monasteries, and historical sites, reflecting the harmony of different religions and cultures.</p>
    <hr>

    <img src="https://unsplash.com/photos/a-group-of-people-that-are-standing-in-front-of-a-crowd-ugsvVsGLZ28"  width = 400  height="200">
    <h2>Nepal Culture</h2>
    <p>Nepal is a multicultural and multilingual country with more than 120 ethnic groups and over 120 languages spoken across
    the nation. The people celebrate various festivals such as Dashain, Tihar, Holi, Buddha Jayanti, and Teej with great
    enthusiasm. Traditional music, dance, art, and cuisine play an important role in Nepalese society. The country's
    national flower is the rhododendron, the national bird is the Himalayan monal (Danphe), and the national animal is the
    cow.</p>
    <hr>

    <img src="https://unsplash.com/photos/assorted-color-temple-miniatures-during-daytime-photo-L4NA2qRqK0s"  width = 400  height="200">
    <h2>Tourism</h2>
    <p>Tourism is one of the major sources of income for Nepal. Every year, visitors from around the world come to experience
    trekking, mountaineering, wildlife safaris, rafting, paragliding, and cultural tours. Popular tourist destinations
    include Kathmandu, Pokhara, Lumbini (the birthplace of Lord Buddha), Chitwan National Park, and the Annapurna and
    Everest regions. Nepal's combination of natural beauty, adventure opportunities, and warm hospitality makes it one of
    the most attractive travel destinations in the world.</p>




